    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-23T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-23T01:00:00-05:00" n="994"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d994">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/391: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-23T15:00:00+09:00"
                            >October 23, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 23—7:12 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>490. Embassy’s 480, October 18, 5 p.m. The British Embassy states that it has
                    received from Tientsin telegram reporting local settlement of the customs issue
                    in accordance with which funds will be deposited in the Yokohama Specie Bank and
                    jurisdiction and regulations of the Maritime Customs will be respected.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
